Hi,

I ran into this problem a few months back..I believe its a 
software problem..the latest version of cantera / python does 
convert the files when the transport file is included

I've converted the Konnov mechanism files for you and attached 
it..

Good luck with everything.

Bhupinder

On Wed Nov 30 12:29:04 EST 2005, mateusz_zb 
<mateusz_zb@...> wrote:

> Dear Friends I have a little problem with loading konnov 
> mechanism. When I call out m-file ck2cti  (f = ck2cti
> ('konmech.inp', 'kontherm.dat', 'kontransport.dat')) in matlab 
> nothing is happening. File .cti is 0 KB and in the file 
> "ck2cti.log" everything is correct and at the end the massage is 
> displayed: "Success... elapsed CPU time = 2.391 s". Matlab is all 
> the time "Busy" and does not working.
> Very interesting is that, when I call out m-file ck2cti (f = 
> ck2cti
> ('konmechcd.inp', 'konthermcd.dat')) without file transport.dat 
> everything is ok and cti file appear but of course without 
> transport properties. All files konmech.inp, therm.dat and 
> transport.dat are from: 
> http://homepages.vub.ac.be/~akonnov/science/mechanism/version0_5.html
> 
> Please help me!!! Maybe somebody have konnov mechanism in cti 
> file? If it is no problem, please send it to me 
> (mateusz_zb@... and mateuszzb@...) Many thanks in 
> advance for help
> 
> Mateusz
